00000200                            
00000200                            ; `0x95DC-0x964C` now looks like a combined inventory/equipment plus magic-menu work area.
00000200                            ; Best fit from the in-ROM strings and control flow around `0x007924-0x00882A`:
00000200                            ; `0x95DC/0x95DD` cache two one-byte magic/status-art selectors mirrored from `0x9F10/0x9F11`,
00000200                            ; while `0x95E0/0x95E4` are now best-fit as a magic-submode modal flag plus saved
00000200                            ; selection index inside the now source-authored upstream loop at `0x00799E-0x007A43`.
00000200                            ; `0x95E5` carries the currently chosen submode value that the same modal-open path writes
00000200                            ; back into per-entry state before it refreshes slot 0/1 status graphics. The next
00000200                            ; source-authored helper block at `0x007CA4-0x007D98` also suggests `0x95E6` is not just a
00000200                            ; generic descriptor pointer: the same word behaves like a page/state selector whose value
00000200                            ; `0x0005` chooses the raw six-spell page, while other values route through the paired
00000200                            ; status-value words at `0x95EE` / `0x95F0` plus a shared `+$08` bias before top-row
00000200                            ; assignments are cleared.
00000200                            ; `0x95B7` / `0x95C8` are now also reused as per-spell empty/filled tile counts while the
00000200                            ; `0x007BB2-0x007CA3` spell-grid refresh draws the six localized spell rows and their paired
00000200                            ; bar strips. `0x959C-0x95A1` now also looks like a small scratch panel/state tuple used by the newly
00000200                            ; source-authored `0x007B22-0x007BA9` status refresh path: `0x959C` feeds the level-style
00000200                            ; two-digit draw, while the later byte at `0x95A2` becomes the slot-2 selector copied into
00000200                            ; `0x95EE`. `0x95D1` now also looks like a layout/config record index consumed by `0x0086BC`; when
00000200                            ; `0x966B` is clear it selects one of seven 6-byte records, and when that page flag is set
00000200                            ; the same value special-cases a smaller two-record table instead.
00000200                            ; The newly source-authored `0x008C34-0x008C7F` tail also snapshots `0x95CE-0x95D0` into
00000200                            ; `0x95D2-0x95D4`, clears the visible-list cursor/scroll/category state, and stores filtered
00000200                            ; copies of the current top-row selector bytes in `0x95E2-0x95E3` whenever `0x9F10/0x9F11`
00000200                            ; still point below the shared `+$08` status-value cutoff.
00000200                            ; `0x95D6` now also looks like the previous category-owned entry id captured before the
00000200                            ; `0x007D9C` visible-list selection flow swaps in a new marked/equipped entry. `0x95DA`
00000200                            ; is a transfer-row scratch byte reused by the adjacent row-upload helpers at
00000200                            ; `0x007E8C-0x007F42`, `0x95DB` is broader than a simple flag and now also acts as an
00000200                            ; arrow-refresh suppression counter during the selected-row blink loop at `0x007E12`, and
00000200                            ; `0x95DE` / `0x95DF` are the matching blink phase countdown/toggle bytes for that same
00000200                            ; effect. `0x95E1` is a scratch byte used by the adjacent status-panel code at `0x00853C` to
00000200                            ; format the likely player level read from `0x9F00`. `0x95E6` is a word-sized base pointer
00000200                            ; consumed by `0x0082F4` when it builds the visible-entry list from category
00000200                            ; availability/equip state bytes at large negative offsets. `0x95E8` holds the measured
00000200                            ; width of the currently selected spell name, `0x95EE` now looks more specifically like a
00000200                            ; lower-row magic/status selector reused by the upstream apply path at `0x007A5A`, `0x95F0`
00000200                            ; is the alternate selector value that the same path swaps in for the second top-row entry,
00000200                            ; and `0x95F8` caches the already-drawn fill amount for the adjacent magic meter.
00000200                            ; `0x963C` now also looks like another saved return vector used by the adjacent top-row
00000200                            ; assignment/clear flow that starts at `0x007E8C`, while `0x9640` / `0x964C` act like scratch
00000200                            ; return/dispatch vectors for the modal submode loop, `0x9648` is the saved return vector
00000200                            ; used by the visible-entry blink loop at `0x007E12`, and `0x9654` is now the matching apply/refresh return vector used by
00000200                            ; `0x007A44-0x007AA8`. `0x95FA` selects headings such as `SELECT`, `WEAPON`, `ARMOR`, `SHIELD`, `BOOTS`,
00000200                            ; `ITEM`, and `MAGIC`; `0x9606-0x9612` track the current list selection and visible
00000200                            ; window; `0x9614-0x9627` drive the blinking list cursor, an auxiliary cursor, and the
00000200                            ; up/down scroll indicators that the selected-input repeat helper updates. The same menu
00000200                            ; cluster also uses `0x966B` as a one-bit page/variant flag that still needs its owner,
00000200                            ; `0x9EF1` bit 4 as a layout-update lock/fallback gate, `0x9EFA/0x9EF2/0x9EF4/0x9EF6` as
00000200                            ; the unpacked destination fields for that 6-byte layout loader, `0x9F10-0x9F11` as
00000200                            ; current top-row status-art selectors, `0x8CDE`, `0x8CE0`, and `0x8CF0` as entry-text width plus two
00000200                            ; tile-row buffers, `0x959F+` as decimal-digit scratch, `0x95DB` as a redraw flag that
00000200                            ; suppresses the post-window arrow refresh, `0x8A77` as a one-byte row id consumed by the
00000200                            ; adjacent text/tile upload helpers around `0x007E8C-0x008000`, and the longword at `0x962C`
00000200                            ; as the likely live gold total.
00000200                            ; Raw ROM work on the still-incbin-backed `0x00882C-0x008C34` continuation keeps the same
00000200                            ; cautious scope. `0x00882C` remaps candidate magic/status ids (`#$28 -> #$0C`, values
00000200                            ; `>= #$2B` minus `#$23`) before clearing matching top-row slots mirrored in `0x9F10/0x9F11`
00000200                            ; and cached in `0x95DC/0x95DD`. `0x00885A` then consumes the pending packed gauge target at
00000200                            ; `0x9628`, selects one of two scale bundles, clamps it against the current packed value at
00000200                            ; `0x9602/0x9604`, and drives the three-row writer at `0x0088D6`. The later `0x008A04`
00000200                            ; continuation still fits best as six-entry spell-bar growth for the localized magic set
00000200                            ; (`FIRE STORM`, `QUAKE`, `THUNDER`, `POWER`, `SHIELD`, `RETURN`) using the inline step table
00000200                            ; `03 03 03 02 02 01`, while `0x008AA2` builds an eight-byte gauge tile-id buffer and
00000200                            ; `0x008BB6` synthesizes follow-on layout widths from the local selection scratch. `0x95B2`
00000200                            ; remains the one-byte fill delta produced when a spell bar grows, `0x95CE-0x95D0` is a
00000200                            ; compact three-byte selection buffer mirrored into `0x95D2-0x95D4`, and
00000200                            ; `0x95F2/0x95F4/0x95F6/0x95FC/0x95FE/0x9600/0x9602/0x9604/0x9628` still form a
00000200                            ; rendering-centric status-gauge work area: animation countdown, two slot widths, body/fill/
00000200                            ; pad tile counts, the current packed value, its low-word remainder component, and a pending
00000200                            ; packed target. The exact game-facing stat meaning still needs more evidence, so those names
00000200                            ; stay display-oriented.
00000200                            ; stay display-oriented.
