0003C6E0                            ; ROM range: 0x03C6E0-0x03FFFF
0003C6E0                            ; Header-like sub-block split inside the final bank020000 compressed/data tail.
0003C6E0                            ;
0003C6E0                            ; These boundaries are weaker than the earlier 0xFF7A/0xFF7B-terminated blocks, but they
0003C6E0                            ; are still useful ROM-order structure: the bytes at 0x03C6E0, 0x03E846, 0x03EF4E,
0003C6E0                            ; 0x03F4D1, and 0x03FE24 each begin with the same short header-like prefixes already seen
0003C6E0                            ; at earlier proven block starts in this tail. Until a caller or decoder proves the exact
0003C6E0                            ; format, keep the ownership conservative and the labels structural.
0003C6E0                            
